<p>For Toledo's cold climate, heating efficiency takes priority over cooling efficiency, though both are important. The most effective systems for Lucas County homes include dual-fuel heat pumps with 16+ SEER cooling ratings and 9.0+ HSPF heating efficiency. These systems use the heat pump for mild weather and switch to gas furnace backup when temperatures drop below 25-30¬∞F, which occurs frequently during Toledo winters. Gas furnaces with 90%+ AFUE ratings paired with 16+ SEER air conditioning units provide excellent performance, with many Toledo contractors recommending 95% AFUE condensing furnaces for maximum efficiency. For homes without natural gas access, cold-climate heat pumps rated for operation down to -15¬∞F, such as those with variable-speed compressors and enhanced vapor injection, offer reliable heating even during Toledo's coldest days while providing efficient cooling during summer months.</p>

